UPTIME(1)                        User Commands                       UPTIME(1)

NAME
       uptime - tell how long the system has been running

SYNOPSIS
       uptime [OPTION]

DESCRIPTION
       Print the current time, how long the system has been running, the
       number of users currently logged on, and the system load averages
       for the past 1, 5, and 15 minutes.

OPTIONS
       -p, --pretty
              show uptime in pretty format (up X days, Y hours,
              Z minutes)

       -s, --since
              system up since, in yyyy-mm-dd HH:MM:SS format

       --help display this help and exit

       -V, --version
              output version information and exit

NOTES
       The number of users is hardcoded to 1 on LikeOS-64.

EXIT STATUS
       0      if OK

       1      if errors occurred

AUTHORS
       LikeOS-64 project.

SEE ALSO
       top(1), free(1), uname(1)

